+## Board Setup (if agent-board MCP is available)
+
+After saving the plan file, immediately create the board hierarchy using the templates in `docs/templates/`. Do this BEFORE offering the execution choice. **Mandatory when `mcp__agent-board__create_epic` is available.**
+
+### Step 1: Upload the plan to the server
+
+```
+upload_doc(
+  file_path: "<absolute local path to the saved plan file>",
+  relative_path: "plans/<filename>.md"
+)
+```
+
+Save the `relative_path` -- use it as `source_doc` in Step 2.
+
+### Step 2: Create the epic
+
+Read `docs/templates/epic-template.md`. Fill every section using content from the plan:
+- **Title**: H1 heading, strip " Implementation Plan" suffix
+- **Context**: the problem being solved (from Goal + Architecture)
+- **Objective**: the Goal sentence verbatim
+- **Value**: why this matters to the project
+- **Success Criteria**: derive from the plan's task outcomes or stated goals
+
+Call `create_epic(project_id, title, description, source_doc=relative_path)`.
+
+### Step 3: Create feature(s)
+
+Read `docs/templates/feature-template.md`. One feature per H2 heading; if no H2 exists, create one feature named after the plan's domain (e.g. "Tasks").
+
+Fill the description from what the feature enables based on the plan context.
+
+Call `create_feature(epic_id, title, description)` for each.
+
+### Step 4: Create stories
+
+Read `docs/templates/story-template.md`. One story per H3 task heading.
+
+- **Title**: H3 heading text
+- **Description**: fill User Story + Acceptance Criteria from the task steps and `- [ ]` lines
+- **estimated_minutes**: step count x 5
+
+Call `create_story(feature_id, title, description, estimated_minutes)` for each task.
+
+**Do not leave template placeholders unfilled. Every field must contain real content derived from the plan.**
+
